  <summary date="2023-03-28T11:52:05Z" status="Introduced in House">Personal Health Investment Today Act of 2023 or the PHIT Act of 2023

This bill allows a medical care tax deduction for up to $1,000 ($2,000 for a joint return or a head of household) of qualified sports and fitness expenses per year. The bill defines qualified sports and fitness expenses as amounts paid exclusively for participating in a physical activity, including (1) fitness facility memberships, (2) physical exercise or activity programs, or (3) equipment for a physical exercise or activity program.</summary>
